lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_5828663\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 16, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104hxr1705401640523.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hxr1705401640523.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hxr1705401640523.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"pyi1665702795358\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                     \n Insert Uniface Objects in the Server Page Layout\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">When creating the layout, elements in the layout must be bound to the component data structure as defined in the Component Editor. You can do this by copying the Uniface objects from the component structure and inserting them as HTML in the layout.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"pyi1665702795358__context_w1882ab1b5b1_w1883ab1b5_w1884ab1\">\n<div class=\"div prereq\" id=\"pyi1665702795358__topic_d12191e1_d12192e1_d12193e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pyi1665702795358__p_d12194e1_d12195e1_d12196e1\">The component structure must be defined before creating the layout. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zii1704964501123.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zii1704964501123.html\" title=\"For services and server pages, use the Define Structure worksheet to add and organize entities and fields in the component structure.\">Define the Component Structure</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"pyi1665702795358__li_d5648e1_d5649e1_d5650e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the Component Editor, click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Design Layout</span>.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"pyi1665702795358__li_d5651e1_d5652e1_d5653e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"pyi1665702795358__p_d12197e1_d12198e1_d12199e1\">In the Structure tab, select the objects you want\n               to insert in the layout, then right-click and choose one of the\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Copy</span> options.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"pyi1665702795358__table_d1265e1_d1266e1_d1267e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Copy as HTML Menu Commands</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"pyi1665702795358__table_d1265e1_d1266e1_d1267e1__entry__1\"> Command </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"pyi1665702795358__table_d1265e1_d1266e1_d1267e1__entry__2\"> Description </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pyi1665702795358__table_d1265e1_d1266e1_d1267e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">As Horizontal\n\t\t\t\t Table</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pyi1665702795358__table_d1265e1_d1266e1_d1267e1__entry__2\">Formats all selected entities and their\n\t\t\t\t content as a horizontal table, with labels in the first row, and entity occurrence data in the\n\t\t\t\t second row. Inner entities are copied as tables within tables.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pyi1665702795358__table_d1265e1_d1266e1_d1267e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">As Unformatted\n\t\t\t\t HTML</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pyi1665702795358__table_d1265e1_d1266e1_d1267e1__entry__2\">Formats the all selected objects as elements\n                     enclosed in <code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;div&gt;</code> tags.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pyi1665702795358__table_d1265e1_d1266e1_d1267e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">As Binding\n\t\t\t\t Information</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pyi1665702795358__table_d1265e1_d1266e1_d1267e1__entry__2\">Formats only the object type and name as an\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">id</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph\">name</code> attribute and its value. For\n                     example, <code class=\"ph codeph\">id=\"ufld:BTN_STORE.ORDERS.SALES\"</code></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pyi1665702795358__p_d12203e1_d12204e1_d12205e1\">The appropriate XHTML is generated and inserted\n                  into the layout.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pyi1665702795358__p_d12206e1_d12207e1_d12208e1\">The generated XHTML for a Dynamic Server Page\n                  contains standards-compliant XHTML. For Static Server Pages, it contains\n                  Uniface-specific elements. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jvt1719471343733.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jvt1719471343733.html\" title=\"Static server page layouts are XHTML-based and include Uniface-specific tags to define the component data structure, as well as standard XHTML for defining the layout and appearance. The structure of the layout is best viewed in the XHTML source.\">Layout of Static Server Pages</a>. </p>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"section result body required-cleanup-multiple-ol-elements-in-topic-body\" id=\"pyi1665702795358__result_w1885ab1b5b5_w1886ab1b5_w1887ab1\">\n<div class=\"sectiondiv postreq\" id=\"pyi1665702795358__topic_d12209e1_d12210e1_d12211e1\">\n<div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"pyi1665702795358__note_w1888ab1b5b5b1b1_w1889ab1b5b5b1_w1890ab1b5b5_w1891ab1b5_w1892ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> Uniface does not synchronize the component structure and server page layout. If you subsequently make changes in the component structure or to widget properties, you also need to update the layout.</div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pmo1665702867768.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>XHTML</a><p>The Extensible HyperText Markup Language (XHTML) is an application of XML in which a document is presented as a structure of nested elements. Along with content, an XHTML document provides its own logical structure without specifying how it should be rendered. Aspects such as font, size, and indentation are therefore determined by the application that interprets the document.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fen1702546666129.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Set Uniface IDE Preferences</a><p>You can configure the behavior of the Uniface IDE by setting preferences in the IDE assignment and initialization files.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5828663\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5828663\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Insert Uniface Objects in the Server Page Layout Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 16, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Insert Uniface Objects in the Server Page Layout When creating the layout, elements in the layout must be bound to the component data structure as defined in the Component Editor. You can do this by copying the Uniface objects from the component structure and inserting them as HTML in the layout. The component structure must be defined before creating the layout. For more information, see Define the Component Structure . In the Component Editor, click Design Layout . In the Structure tab, select the objects you want to insert in the layout, then right-click and choose one of the Copy options. Table 1. Copy as HTML Menu Commands Command Description As Horizontal Table Formats all selected entities and their content as a horizontal table, with labels in the first row, and entity occurrence data in the second row. Inner entities are copied as tables within tables. As Unformatted HTML Formats the all selected objects as elements enclosed in <div> tags. As Binding Information Formats only the object type and name as an id or name attribute and its value. For example, id=\"ufld:BTN_STORE.ORDERS.SALES\" The appropriate XHTML is generated and inserted into the layout. The generated XHTML for a Dynamic Server Page contains standards-compliant XHTML. For Static Server Pages, it contains Uniface-specific elements. For more information, see Layout of Static Server Pages . CAUTION: Uniface does not synchronize the component structure and server page layout. If you subsequently make changes in the component structure or to widget properties, you also need to update the layout. Related Links XHTML The Extensible HyperText Markup Language (XHTML) is an application of XML in which a document is presented as a structure of nested elements. Along with content, an XHTML document provides its own logical structure without specifying how it should be rendered. Aspects such as font, size, and indentation are therefore determined by the application that interprets the document. Set Uniface IDE Preferences You can configure the behavior of the Uniface IDE by setting preferences in the IDE assignment and initialization files. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}